{{Infobox power station | name = Cårrujavrit Power Station | name_official = ''Cårrujavrit kraftverk'' | image = | location_map = Troms | location_map_caption = Location in [[Troms]] county | coordinates = {{coord|69|41|30|N|22|09|39|E|type:landmark|display=inline,title}} | location = [[Kvænangen]], [[Troms]] | country = Norway | owner = Kvænangen Kraftverk AS | status = O | psps_upper_res = | psps_upper_res_capacity= | psps_penstocks = | psps_lower_res = | psps_lower_res_capacity= | psps_hydraulic_head = 305&nbsp;m | psps_generators = 1 | psps_pumpgenerators = 0 | psps_pumps = 0 | ps_units_operational = | ps_units_manu_model = | ps_units_uc = | ps_units_planned = | ps_units_cancelled = | ps_units_decommissioned= | ps_electrical_capacity = 1.7 | ps_electrical_cap_fac = 73.9%<!-- 11,000 MWh/year / ( 1.7 MW * 365 days/year * 24h/day) = 0.739 --> | ps_annual_generation = 11 | ps_annual_gen_year = | website = | extra = }}
The '''Cårrujavrit Hydroelectric Power Station''' ({{lang-no|Cårrujavrit kraftverk}} or ''Čårrujavrit kraftverk''<ref>[https://www.regjeringen.no/no/dokumenter/verneplan-for-kvanangsbotn-og-navitdalen/id633556/ Verneplan for Kvænangsbotn og Navitdalen: Etablering av Kvænangsbotn og Navitdalen landskapsvernområder i Kvænangen Kommune, Troms Fylke. 2011. p. 7ff.]</ref>) is a [[hydroelectricity|hydroelectric]] [[power station]] in the municipality of [[Kvænangen]] in [[Troms]] [[Counties of Norway|county]], [[Norway]]. It utilizes a drop of {{convert|305|m|sp=us}} between its intake reservoir on the Njemenaiko River ({{lang-no|Njemenaikoelva}}, {{lang-fkv|Niemenaikunjoki}}, {{lang-se|Njemenjáikojohka}})<ref>[http://www.kvenskestedsnavn.no/stedsnavn/view/5901 Kvensk stedsnavndatabase: Niemenaikunjoki.]</ref> and Little Lakes ({{lang-no|Småvatnan}}, {{lang-fkv|Pikkujärvet}}, {{lang-se|Čorrojávrrit}}),<ref>[http://www.kvenskestedsnavn.no/stedsnavn/view/5968 Kvensk stedsnavndatabase: Pikkujärvet.]</ref> which is also the reservoir for the [[Kvænangsbotn Hydroelectric Power Station]]. [[Šuoikkatjávri|Lake Tjoika]] ({{lang-fkv|Sueikkajärvi}} or ''Hyttysenjärvi'', {{lang-se|Šuoikkatjávri}})<ref>[http://www.kvenskestedsnavn.no/stedsnavn/view/6110 Kvensk stedsnavndatabase: Sueikkajärvi.]</ref> serves as the reservoir for the plant and is regulated at a level between {{cvt|529|m|sp=us}} and {{cvt|516|m|sp=us}}. The plant has a [[Francis turbine]] and operates at an installed capacity of {{nowrap|1.7 [[Megawatt|MW]]}}, with an average annual production of about 11&nbsp;GWh. The plant is controlled by Kvænangen Kraftverk AS, with a 48.2% share owned by Troms Kraft.<ref>[http://www.tromskraft.no/om/selskap/tkp/kraftverk Troms Kraft: Våre kraftverk.] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151119040058/http://www.tromskraft.no/om/selskap/tkp/kraftverk |date=2015-11-19 }}</ref>
