The '''Spherical Tokamak Experiment''' ({{lang-pt|'''ETE''' - '''Experimento Tokamak Esférico'''}}) is a machine dedicated to plasma studies in low aspect ratio [[tokamak]]s. The ETE was entirely designed and assembled at the Associated Plasma Laboratory (Laboratório Associado de Plasma, LAP) of Brazil's [[National Institute for Space Research]] (INPE).<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Ludwig|first=Gerson Otto|last2=Andrade|first2=Maria Celia Ramos de|last3=Barbosa|first3=Luis Filipe Wiltgen|date=1999|title=The ETE spherical Tokamak project|url=http://inis.iaea.org/Search/search.aspx?orig_q=RN:36076128|language=English}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|last=Ludwig|first=G. O.|last2=Del Bosco|first2=E.|last3=Ferreira|first3=J. G.|last4=Berni|first4=L. A.|last5=Oliveira|first5=R. M.|last6=Andrade|first6=M. C. R.|last7=Shibata|first7=C. S.|last8=Ueda|first8=M.|last9=Barbosa|first9=L. F. W.|date=Dec 2003|title=Spherical tokamak development in Brazil|url=http://www.scielo.br/scielo.php?script=sci_abstract&pid=S0103-97332003000400041&lng=en&nrm=iso&tlng=en|journal=Brazilian Journal of Physics|volume=33|issue=4|pages=848–859|doi=10.1590/S0103-97332003000400041|issn=0103-9733|via=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|last=Ludwig|first=G.O|last2=Bosco|first2=E. Del|last3=Ferreira|first3=J.G|date=2005-06-30|title=Eddy currents in the vacuum vessel of the ETE spherical tokamak|journal=Nuclear Fusion|volume=45|issue=7|pages=675–684|doi=10.1088/0029-5515/45/7/017|issn=0029-5515}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|last=Ludwig|first=Gerson Otto|date=Sep 1997|title=Theoretical Methods in the Design of the Poloidal Field Coils for the ETE Spherical Tokamak|url=http://www.scielo.br/scielo.php?script=sci_abstract&pid=S0103-97331997000300009&lng=en&nrm=iso&tlng=en|journal=Brazilian Journal of Physics|volume=27|issue=3|pages=|doi=10.1590/S0103-97331997000300009|issn=0103-9733|via=}}</ref>

